The paper proposes a new class of selection networks for encoding boolean cardinality constraints. This involves algorithms for selecting and merging elements, which are relevant to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the theoretical and experimental evaluation of the proposed encoding, which is relevant to the sub-categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and programming languages (cs.PL).
